# Copywriting — no em dash (—)

Do **not** use the em dash (—) in site copy, UI strings, SEO text, or marketing content unless it is strictly necessary (rare).

Em dashes are often read as generic “AI slop”; prefer natural French/English punctuation:

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `X — Y` (contrast / aside) | comma, colon, or parentheses |
| `X — voici…` | `X : voici…` |
| Title / SEO separator | pipe `\|` or colon `:` |
| `Phase 1 — Title` | `Phase 1 : Title` |
| CTA prefix `— sans engagement` | `Sans engagement` (no leading dash) |
| Glued `word—word` | comma or rephrase |

**Examples**

- ❌ `livrer — pas seulement exécuter`
- ✅ `livrer, pas seulement exécuter`

- ❌ `Situations — accompagnement produit`
- ✅ `Situations \| accompagnement produit` (SEO) or `Situations : accompagnement produit`

When editing `public/locales/`, scan for `—` (U+2014) before finishing.
